{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"acardiac-clotty-hornbill","description":"# Enable public GitHub intake: Issues on, Go-style issue forms, SUPPORT.md\n\n## Why\n\nGitHub Issues are disabled on navapbc/rebar (verified via API 2026-07-09: `has_issues: false`), so outsiders have no zero-friction way to report bugs or request features. Go demonstrates the convergent mirror pattern: code review on Gerrit, Issues canonical on GitHub — filing a bug requires zero Gerrit onboarding. Enabling Issues is the highest-leverage, lowest-cost community change; all three assessments converge on it.\n\n## What\n\n- Flip `has_issues=true` on navapbc/rebar (Settings or PATCH `/repos/navapbc/rebar`). Leave Discussions OFF (convergent single-maintainer advice: one inbox, no community to self-answer; issue→discussion conversion is one click if ever needed — record as a reversible decision).\n- Rework `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/` to Go-style numeric-ordered issue forms:\n  - `00-bug.yml` — required rebar version, required environment textarea (`rebar --version` etc., `render: shell`), required did/saw/expected; `labels: [\"bug\", \"needs-triage\"]`.\n  - `10-feature.yml` — problem statement + proposal textareas; `labels: [\"enhancement\", \"needs-triage\"]`.\n  - `20-question.yml` — `labels: [\"question\"]`; unlike Go, questions stay IN Issues (rebar has no forum to redirect to).\n- `config.yml`: `blank_issues_enabled: false` (no triage team to absorb free-form issues) + `contact_links`: (a) Gerrit — \"Code changes / patches: this repo is a read-only mirror; code review happens on Gerrit, see CONTRIBUTING.md\" → https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com; (b) Security — private reporting per SECURITY.md, never a public issue. The Gerrit contact_link is load-bearing: the chooser is exactly where a would-be PR author lands.\n- Add `SUPPORT.md` (kubernetes + vscode-jupyter hybrid, rendered by GitHub as a banner above the new-issue chooser): what Issues are for, search first, code changes → Gerrit, single-maintainer best-effort / no SLA.\n- Create labels: `needs-triage`, `waiting-for-info` (Go's label state machine, scaled down; stale-close automation deferred).\n\n## Scope\n\nIN: repo settings flip, `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/*` rework (bug_report.yml / feature_request.yml / config.yml exist today — rework in place, don't duplicate), `SUPPORT.md`, labels.\nOUT: GitHub Issues ↔ rebar-store sync (separate epic slimy-tuber-stoop, linked relates_to); enabling Discussions; stale-bot automation; issue-creation rate limiting (premature until abuse appears).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `has_issues: true` live on navapbc/rebar; the new-issue chooser shows 3 forms + 2 contact links; blank issues disabled.\n- [ ] Bug form mechanically enforces version + environment (`render: shell`) + did/saw/expected; all forms auto-apply their labels.\n- [ ] `SUPPORT.md` present, rendered on the chooser, stating the mirror + Gerrit routing and support expectations (best-effort, no SLA).\n- [ ] Existing template content preserved where still accurate; obsolete fields dropped deliberately, not silently.\n- [ ] Decision recorded on the ticket: Discussions stay off at launch (reversible; revisit trigger = question-issues clogging the tracker).","id":"71b0-8c03-3961-4863","parent_id":"fc2a-9fa5-def6-4e68","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Enable public GitHub intake: Issues on, Go-style issue forms, SUPPORT.md"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783628663115749001,"uuid":"202cbbe4-093b-4386-9ba0-83fa2e46ac97"}